WEBVTT

1
00:00:05.673 --> 00:00:07.666
[people chattering]

2
00:00:09.000 --> 00:00:15.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

3
00:00:20.154 --> 00:00:22.547
All right. you two.
There you go. Enjoy.

4
00:00:22.683 --> 00:00:24.754
[Moon Yeong] No. no!
Uh. p-please!

5
00:00:24.890 --> 00:00:26.888
[cries] Do not do this!

6
00:00:27.023 --> 00:00:29.655
[speaking Korean]

7
00:00:32.362 --> 00:00:34.330
[in English] Please...
Miles.

8
00:00:35.262 --> 00:00:36.561
P-Please! Please!

9
00:00:36.697 --> 00:00:40.098
My husband not do this!
Not do this! Help!

10
00:00:40.233 --> 00:00:41.968
- [Palmer] We're just
doing our jobs.
- What the hell?

11
00:00:42.103 --> 00:00:43.569
Help! Help!

12
00:00:43.704 --> 00:00:45.107
- What's going on?
- Back up. buddy.

13
00:00:45.243 --> 00:00:47.004
[Moon Yeong]
Husband do not do this!

14
00:00:47.139 --> 00:00:49.471
Wh-Why would they
arrest Lee?
I don't know.

15
00:00:49.606 --> 00:00:51.649
- Stay clear. Stand clear.
- [Moon Yeong sobs]
Someone help!

16
00:00:51.784 --> 00:00:54.543
Do you think this could be
about the murder?
No fucking way.

17
00:00:54.679 --> 00:00:57.321
- He not do this.
We're friends. Help.
- Can't you do something. Dad?

18
00:00:57.456 --> 00:00:59.056
- Not without being arrested.
- Help! [pants]

19
00:00:59.191 --> 00:01:00.925
- [Palmer] Step back.
- Help!

20
00:01:01.060 --> 00:01:02.820
- No. Don't.
- [in Korean]

21
00:01:02.955 --> 00:01:05.022
[in English] Hey. hey.
That's her husband.

22
00:01:05.158 --> 00:01:06.923
- [bystander 1] That's Lee.
- [bystanders chattering]

23
00:01:07.059 --> 00:01:09.926
Dispatch. Unit 37.
Possible civil disturbance

24
00:01:10.061 --> 00:01:12.261
in business district.
Backup requested.

25
00:01:12.396 --> 00:01:14.667
- This gathering exceeds
the legal limit...
- [crowd muttering]

26
00:01:14.803 --> 00:01:16.968
...and now constitutes
an unlawful assembly.

27
00:01:17.971 --> 00:01:21.377
Anyone who fails to disperse
will be arrested.

28
00:02:55.501 --> 00:02:58.610
[keyboard typing]

29
00:02:58.745 --> 00:03:01.477
[radio chatter]

30
00:03:13.156 --> 00:03:14.325
[Shireen] Whoa...

31
00:03:15.191 --> 00:03:17.060
Um. hey. boss?

32
00:03:17.196 --> 00:03:18.994
[Walt] Yeah. Reen. What's up?

33
00:03:19.130 --> 00:03:20.358
Take a look at this.

34
00:03:20.493 --> 00:03:22.663
It's glitchy but...

35
00:03:32.808 --> 00:03:35.275
Get this to Houston ASAP.
And to Dev.

36
00:03:35.411 --> 00:03:36.705
He's gonna wanna see this.

37
00:03:36.841 --> 00:03:38.716
[phone keyboard clicking]

38
00:03:38.851 --> 00:03:39.977
[chuckles]

39
00:03:41.147 --> 00:03:43.488
[Aleida] Now keep in mind.
this data is incomplete.

40
00:03:43.623 --> 00:03:45.387
The S.E.E.K.E.R.s only gave us
a partial data stream.

41
00:03:45.522 --> 00:03:47.719
but we are seeing
strong evidence

42
00:03:47.855 --> 00:03:49.784
that something's making
proteins on Titan.

43
00:03:50.420 --> 00:03:53.162
Now. I hate to say it's life
before we're sure.

44
00:03:53.297 --> 00:03:54.558
so let's make goddamn sure.

45
00:03:55.328 --> 00:03:57.895
And I don't want to hear about
any of this getting out.

46
00:03:58.631 --> 00:04:01.300
We have a head start
on our competitors.
Can't let that slip away.

47
00:04:02.036 --> 00:04:03.836
[inhales sharply] All right.
let's get to work.

48
00:04:05.569 --> 00:04:06.806
[sighs]

49
00:04:17.453 --> 00:04:18.580
<i> Can you believe it?</i>

50
00:04:19.349 --> 00:04:21.359
<i> Walt may have found</i>
<i> life. Kelly.</i>

51
00:04:22.392 --> 00:04:23.659
[gasps]
<i> Life.</i>

52
00:04:24.195 --> 00:04:25.326
This could be huge.

53
00:04:25.928 --> 00:04:28.461
<i> Right? Get back here</i>
<i> as soon as you can.</i>

54
00:04:28.597 --> 00:04:29.928
<i> Dev wants to talk to you.</i>

55
00:04:31.899 --> 00:04:35.373
[sighs] Holy shit.
[exhales sharply]

56
00:04:37.241 --> 00:04:39.938
[door opens. closes]

57
00:04:47.954 --> 00:04:48.918
[static crackles]

58
00:04:49.053 --> 00:04:51.048
[radio chatter]

59
00:05:00.562 --> 00:05:02.400
- [device beeps]
- [sighs]

60
00:05:04.837 --> 00:05:07.163
Can I help you?
Yeah. I'm here
to see Lee Jung-Gil.

61
00:05:07.866 --> 00:05:09.698
Not possible.
Why not?

62
00:05:09.833 --> 00:05:12.474
Sheriff James has revoked
all visitation until
further notice.

63
00:05:12.610 --> 00:05:14.246
That's bullshit.
He can't do that.

64
00:05:14.381 --> 00:05:17.314
Well. if you'd like to.
uh. file an appeal.

65
00:05:17.917 --> 00:05:21.320
fill out this form.
check back with us
in a day or two.

66
00:05:40.566 --> 00:05:41.571
[grunts]

67
00:05:43.744 --> 00:05:44.739
[grunts]

68
00:05:46.011 --> 00:05:47.203
[chuckles]

69
00:05:49.144 --> 00:05:51.779
Ed. you know you can't
take off your ankle monitor.

70
00:06:01.787 --> 00:06:02.988
What are you doing here?

71
00:06:03.689 --> 00:06:04.957
I came to see you.

72
00:06:08.501 --> 00:06:10.094
You think I was just
gonna sit back

73
00:06:10.229 --> 00:06:12.602
and let you rot in here
all by your lonesome?

74
00:06:14.174 --> 00:06:15.702
I do not know what to say.

75
00:06:15.838 --> 00:06:17.371
Well. you can start
by telling me

76
00:06:17.507 --> 00:06:19.136
what the hell is going on.

77
00:06:19.271 --> 00:06:21.039
You know they're saying
you killed this guy.

78
00:06:22.008 --> 00:06:24.579
[breathes heavily]
I did fight him.

79
00:06:24.715 --> 00:06:26.913
Remember the man
I told you about?

80
00:06:32.191 --> 00:06:33.452
But I swear to you...

81
00:06:33.587 --> 00:06:35.026
[breathes heavily]

82
00:06:35.161 --> 00:06:36.924
...I didn't kill him.

83
00:06:37.794 --> 00:06:39.156
Your word's
good enough for me.

84
00:06:40.364 --> 00:06:42.401
[breathing heavily]

85
00:06:45.303 --> 00:06:46.735
Hey.
Thank you.

86
00:06:47.665 --> 00:06:48.704
Buddy.

87
00:06:50.934 --> 00:06:52.169
It'll be okay.

88
00:06:53.604 --> 00:06:56.276
There's a lot of people out
there that are pulling for you.

89
00:06:56.411 --> 00:06:57.647
care about you.

90
00:06:58.483 --> 00:06:59.845
- That'll testify.
- Don't.

91
00:06:59.981 --> 00:07:02.850
- Trial will not be here.
- What?

92
00:07:02.985 --> 00:07:05.084
Yeah. They are moving me
to... [inhales sharply]

93
00:07:05.219 --> 00:07:07.386
- ...neutral country.
- I know the M-6 Charter.

94
00:07:07.522 --> 00:07:09.827
They can't send you back
to Earth without holding
a hearing here first.

95
00:07:09.963 --> 00:07:12.924
Because of my status they say
the rules do not apply to me.

96
00:07:13.059 --> 00:07:14.994
They are putting me
on next transport.

97
00:07:15.629 --> 00:07:17.964
Ed. promise me...

98
00:07:19.968 --> 00:07:21.406
you will take care
of Nam Moon Yeong.

99
00:07:21.541 --> 00:07:23.101
Okay. no. [stammers]
Enough of that.

100
00:07:24.573 --> 00:07:25.873
You're not going back.

101
00:07:27.546 --> 00:07:32.979
["Stormy Weather"
plays on radio]

102
00:07:43.328 --> 00:07:44.320
[Lily] It's bullshit.

103
00:07:45.230 --> 00:07:46.355
Sending him back.

104
00:07:47.024 --> 00:07:48.231
It's all just so crazy.

105
00:07:48.367 --> 00:07:49.692
Well. that's how it works.

106
00:07:50.328 --> 00:07:52.102
You break the rules.
you go back.

107
00:07:52.238 --> 00:07:53.736
Remember Sam's dad?

108
00:07:55.032 --> 00:07:56.233
Yeah.
it's fucked up.

109
00:07:57.270 --> 00:07:58.805
I mean. if they're
saying Lee did this

110
00:07:58.941 --> 00:08:01.739
then he should be tried
here by Marsies.

111
00:08:01.875 --> 00:08:05.581
Yeah. I mean.
i-if he gets sent down there
he'll be convicted for sure.

112
00:08:05.717 --> 00:08:08.248
- Maybe he should be.
- [chuckles]

113
00:08:08.384 --> 00:08:10.917
What? Oh. come on.
There's no way
he killed that guy.

114
00:08:11.053 --> 00:08:13.284
And you're basing this
on what exactly?

115
00:08:13.419 --> 00:08:15.318
Well. I can't tell you
how many times my parents

116
00:08:15.454 --> 00:08:17.320
have had him and Moon Yeong
over for dinner.

117
00:08:17.455 --> 00:08:18.924
Yeah. I-I've known him
since I was eight.

118
00:08:19.059 --> 00:08:20.697
I never once
saw him get angry.

119
00:08:20.832 --> 00:08:22.424
I mean. he never even
raised his voice.

120
00:08:22.559 --> 00:08:24.701
Come on. Alex.
That's a little naive. no?

121
00:08:24.837 --> 00:08:26.966
The nice man who gave you candy
when you were little

122
00:08:27.101 --> 00:08:28.802
couldn't possibly
do something bad?

123
00:08:28.938 --> 00:08:30.574
[Lily] I hear
what you're saying

124
00:08:30.710 --> 00:08:33.040
but it's-it's not
like that. Lee is...

125
00:08:33.175 --> 00:08:37.646
He's so gentle
and affectionate
with his wife.

126
00:08:37.782 --> 00:08:40.377
And I just...
I just don't see it.

127
00:08:40.512 --> 00:08:42.779
Isn't that what they always say
about serial killers?

128
00:08:43.616 --> 00:08:46.857
"He was such a nice man.
So considerate to
his neighbors."

129
00:08:46.993 --> 00:08:49.692
Until they found
a dozen dead bodies
buried in his backyard.

130
00:08:49.828 --> 00:08:52.058
But then by that logic
you can't trust anyone.

131
00:08:53.461 --> 00:08:54.496
Ever.

132
00:08:54.631 --> 00:08:56.498
Welcome to the Soviet Union.

133
00:08:56.633 --> 00:08:58.966
["Stormy Weather" continues]

134
00:09:00.073 --> 00:09:01.067
[lighter flicks]

135
00:09:02.473 --> 00:09:04.466
[patrons chattering]

136
00:09:11.008 --> 00:09:12.210
[inhales sharply]

137
00:09:13.950 --> 00:09:16.814
You okay. hon?
It's just not right.

138
00:09:16.949 --> 00:09:19.384
- This is his home.
he should get to stay up here.
- [phone buzzes]

139
00:09:19.519 --> 00:09:23.051
[sighs] I can't believe they're
sending him back Earthside.

140
00:09:23.187 --> 00:09:26.723
Everyone's pissed.
You know. maybe we should
get everyone here tonight.

141
00:09:26.859 --> 00:09:28.226
Talk about it.

142
00:09:29.960 --> 00:09:33.363
Yeah. good idea.
I'm gonna head to
the loading dock.

143
00:09:36.309 --> 00:09:38.302
[chattering continues]

144
00:09:48.219 --> 00:09:49.346
[sighs]

145
00:09:56.557 --> 00:09:57.552
[sighs]

146
00:10:04.600 --> 00:10:05.896
Thanks for coming.

147
00:10:06.532 --> 00:10:09.067
Thought I'd pick some place
nostalgic for you.

148
00:10:09.203 --> 00:10:11.071
I told you to stop
contacting me.

149
00:10:12.344 --> 00:10:13.535
What do you want?

150
00:10:15.838 --> 00:10:18.116
That was some shit show
with Lee yesterday. huh?

151
00:10:18.251 --> 00:10:19.546
Are you surprised?

152
00:10:20.182 --> 00:10:22.181
It's bullshit. There's
no way he killed that man.

153
00:10:23.857 --> 00:10:27.052
- I know Lee was well-liked.
- Is well-liked.

154
00:10:27.188 --> 00:10:28.591
That's what I said.
No. it wasn't.

155
00:10:28.727 --> 00:10:30.090
All right. well.
either way.

156
00:10:31.888 --> 00:10:34.923
You always seem to have
your finger on the pulse.

157
00:10:35.058 --> 00:10:36.363
So to speak.

158
00:10:36.966 --> 00:10:39.170
So. we need
your help again.

159
00:10:39.306 --> 00:10:40.602
Should I be worried?

160
00:10:41.605 --> 00:10:43.834
Maybe you should be worried
about whether you got
the right guy.

161
00:10:43.970 --> 00:10:45.406
Look. what I don't want.

162
00:10:46.042 --> 00:10:48.245
and what I think
you don't want.

163
00:10:48.380 --> 00:10:49.544
is another riot.

164
00:10:50.180 --> 00:10:52.584
And temperatures are running
damn high right now.

165
00:10:53.453 --> 00:10:58.448
And I need to know
if there's anyone agitating
for any sort of violence.

166
00:10:59.559 --> 00:11:00.890
No one wants
more violence.

167
00:11:02.225 --> 00:11:04.228
And I told you before.
I'm not gonna help you.

168
00:11:04.897 --> 00:11:08.493
Now. my deal with them.
was just the once.

169
00:11:08.629 --> 00:11:10.933
then they said they would
leave me and my family alone.

170
00:11:11.068 --> 00:11:13.304
Yeah. well.
circumstances have changed.

171
00:11:14.274 --> 00:11:18.076
This Lee business has caused
some consternation
down on Earth.

172
00:11:19.346 --> 00:11:22.780
We need to make sure
that things don't repeat
themselves up here.

173
00:11:24.409 --> 00:11:25.684
That sounds like
a you problem.

174
00:11:29.012 --> 00:11:31.179
How do you think your friends
would feel if they found out

175
00:11:31.315 --> 00:11:32.581
what you did back in '03?

176
00:11:35.284 --> 00:11:36.288
What did you say?

177
00:11:37.593 --> 00:11:38.955
[chuckles]

178
00:11:39.090 --> 00:11:40.362
All those people.

179
00:11:41.298 --> 00:11:43.496
Well. they just think
you're God's gift. Don't they?

180
00:11:43.631 --> 00:11:47.563
- [scoffs]
- Imagine how disappointed
they'd all be.

181
00:11:49.136 --> 00:11:51.039
Not to mention
your daughters.

182
00:11:53.108 --> 00:11:54.636
The way
they look up to you.

183
00:11:57.145 --> 00:11:58.481
How do you think
they'd feel

184
00:11:59.117 --> 00:12:01.379
if they found out you
sold out your friends?

185
00:12:07.926 --> 00:12:09.827
We both want
the same thing. Miles.

186
00:12:10.363 --> 00:12:12.621
Peace and quiet.

187
00:12:14.299 --> 00:12:17.329
Now. I'm sure
if you hear of
any trouble brewing.

188
00:12:18.999 --> 00:12:20.332
you'll let me know.

189
00:12:32.045 --> 00:12:34.582
[breathing heavily]

190
00:12:34.717 --> 00:12:37.181
[news anchor]
<i> Governor Polivanov</i>
<i> was quick to announce</i>

191
00:12:37.316 --> 00:12:41.058
<i> that an arrest has been made</i>
<i> in the Red Planet's</i>
<i> first homicide.</i>

192
00:12:41.194 --> 00:12:43.851
<i> Known around the world</i>
<i> as the first man on Mars.</i>

193
00:12:43.987 --> 00:12:46.396
<i> Lee Jung-Gil has been</i>
<i> charged with murder.</i>

194
00:12:47.066 --> 00:12:49.263
<i> Lee defected</i>
<i> from North Korea in 2004</i>

195
00:12:49.399 --> 00:12:51.935
<i> after his home country</i>
<i> was voted out of the M-7</i>

196
00:12:52.070 --> 00:12:54.369
<i> and forced to leave</i>
<i> Happy Valley.</i>

197
00:12:54.504 --> 00:12:57.499
<i> He's accused of killing</i>
<i> a fellow North Korean man.</i>

198
00:12:57.635 --> 00:13:01.104
<i> It is unclear at this time</i>
<i> what motive may have driven</i>
<i> the former ujunaut.</i>

199
00:13:01.239 --> 00:13:04.973
<i> but authorities suspect</i>
<i> it may have been over</i>
<i> a romantic dispute.</i>

200
00:13:05.742 --> 00:13:09.515
<i> The crime has also put</i>
<i> a spotlight on Happy Valley's</i>
<i> undocumented residents.</i>

201
00:13:09.651 --> 00:13:12.623
<i> Many are concerned that</i>
<i> the growing number of craters.</i>

202
00:13:12.758 --> 00:13:16.885
<i> those who came to Mars</i>
<i> illegally and live outside</i>
<i> of the base's legal framework.</i>

203
00:13:17.021 --> 00:13:19.890
<i> is leading to an increase</i>
<i> in crime on the base.</i>

204
00:13:20.025 --> 00:13:22.966
<i> Statistics do not necessarily</i>
<i> support these concerns.</i>

205
00:13:23.102 --> 00:13:25.002
<i> but nonetheless.</i>
<i> many residents state</i>

206
00:13:25.138 --> 00:13:28.001
<i> that they feel less safe</i>
<i> over the past months.</i>

207
00:13:28.136 --> 00:13:29.732
<i> Governor Polivanov emphasized</i>

208
00:13:29.868 --> 00:13:32.638
<i> that no crime will go</i>
<i> unpunished on his watch</i>

209
00:13:32.774 --> 00:13:36.342
<i> and Lee will be on a transport</i>
<i> back to Earth to stand trial.</i>

210
00:13:38.684 --> 00:13:41.581
- [people chattering]
- [Dev] I'm sorry but
there's nothing I can do.

211
00:13:41.716 --> 00:13:43.479
My hands are tied.
The M-6 Charter
clearly states--

212
00:13:43.615 --> 00:13:45.418
Oh. no. Come on.
Fuck the charter!

213
00:13:45.554 --> 00:13:47.586
This is the first man on Mars
we're talking about.

214
00:13:47.721 --> 00:13:49.822
They don't care if he's
the second coming of Christ.

215
00:13:49.957 --> 00:13:52.096
They will not
make an exception.
I've already looked into it.

216
00:13:52.698 --> 00:13:55.694
- Bribe someone.
- They'd love for me to try
something foolish like that.

217
00:13:55.830 --> 00:13:58.026
Then they can send me packing
for Earth right alongside Lee.

218
00:13:58.161 --> 00:14:00.166
Oh. come on.
They'd never come
after you. You're--

219
00:14:00.302 --> 00:14:02.401
My position is not
as strong as you think.

220
00:14:03.104 --> 00:14:05.672
They'd been handing out
contracts to my competitors
left and right.

221
00:14:05.807 --> 00:14:08.605
Like Kuragin with that
space elevator. They're
trying to push me out.

222
00:14:08.740 --> 00:14:10.343
[Ed] So all the more reason
to fight 'em.

223
00:14:10.479 --> 00:14:12.315
Sometimes you have
to pick your battles. Ed.

224
00:14:12.851 --> 00:14:14.845
We wouldn't have this asteroid

225
00:14:14.980 --> 00:14:18.819
or any of this if it wasn't for
Lee Jung-Gil and you know it.

226
00:14:18.955 --> 00:14:21.683
And I will do everything
in my power to protect him
once he's on Earth.

227
00:14:21.819 --> 00:14:23.522
I've already hired
the best legal team.

228
00:14:23.657 --> 00:14:25.963
Oh. it doesn't matter
how goddamn good they are.

229
00:14:26.098 --> 00:14:28.328
If Lee gets sent to Earth.
he's a dead man.

230
00:14:30.136 --> 00:14:32.202
You remember what happened
to Svetlana Zakharova

231
00:14:32.338 --> 00:14:35.700
when they sent her down to
Earth to stand trial in India.

232
00:14:35.835 --> 00:14:38.200
I remember.
She hung herself
in a jail cell.

233
00:14:38.335 --> 00:14:40.340
No. she did not.

234
00:14:41.977 --> 00:14:43.541
She'd never do that.

235
00:14:45.211 --> 00:14:46.544
Soviets had her killed.

236
00:14:48.612 --> 00:14:50.680
And if Lee gets sent to Earth.

237
00:14:50.815 --> 00:14:52.891
the North Koreans
will do the same to him.

238
00:14:55.891 --> 00:14:56.961
Come on. Dev.

239
00:14:59.993 --> 00:15:00.989
I'm sorry. Ed.

240
00:15:01.858 --> 00:15:03.497
I'm sorry
there's nothing I can do.

241
00:15:04.033 --> 00:15:05.431
[Malka]
Nothing you can do?

242
00:15:06.531 --> 00:15:07.736
After all he did
for you?

243
00:15:07.872 --> 00:15:09.340
He didn't do it for me.

244
00:15:09.976 --> 00:15:12.009
He did it for himself
and his wife.

245
00:15:12.144 --> 00:15:14.840
[scoffs] You're
a cold-blooded bastard.

246
00:15:14.975 --> 00:15:17.909
I have to be.
You have to be too
to get what you want.

247
00:15:18.879 --> 00:15:22.453
This is what we fought for.
What I'm still fighting for.

248
00:15:23.123 --> 00:15:25.014
Meru will be a beacon
of freedom for us all.

249
00:15:25.149 --> 00:15:27.724
but to build it
I need to be thinking
three. four steps ahead.

250
00:15:27.860 --> 00:15:30.694
And if I give them any excuse.
the M-6 will swoop down
and snatch it all away from us.

251
00:15:30.830 --> 00:15:32.259
That's all well and good. Dev.

252
00:15:32.394 --> 00:15:34.257
But while you're up here
playing with LEGOs.

253
00:15:34.393 --> 00:15:35.928
Lee's life is on the line.

254
00:15:36.664 --> 00:15:39.267
And I. for one.
will not abandon my friend.

255
00:16:21.878 --> 00:16:22.981
[knocking on door]

256
00:16:28.885 --> 00:16:29.988
May I come in?

257
00:16:41.859 --> 00:16:43.661
I'd like to talk to you
about Yoon Tae-Min.

258
00:16:46.138 --> 00:16:48.335
To make more trouble
for my husband?

259
00:16:48.470 --> 00:16:51.103
No. A-Actually
to find out the truth.

260
00:16:51.239 --> 00:16:52.833
Truth is what officer say.

261
00:16:52.969 --> 00:16:54.811
[sighs] Maybe
where you came from

262
00:16:54.947 --> 00:16:56.872
but that's not how it is here.

263
00:16:57.007 --> 00:16:59.884
Then why...
why is my husband arrested?

264
00:17:00.020 --> 00:17:01.614
That's what I want
to understand.

265
00:17:02.150 --> 00:17:03.552
He did not do this.

266
00:17:04.222 --> 00:17:05.650
How'd your husband
know Mr. Yoon?

267
00:17:07.286 --> 00:17:09.621
He Korean like us.

268
00:17:10.955 --> 00:17:14.293
We try to help people like Yoon
when they arrive.

269
00:17:14.428 --> 00:17:17.100
Get him job.
Get him money.

270
00:17:17.235 --> 00:17:20.302
But then.
trouble come between them.

271
00:17:21.640 --> 00:17:22.836
Why trouble?

272
00:17:22.971 --> 00:17:24.240
My husband.

273
00:17:26.008 --> 00:17:27.839
he's man of pride.

274
00:17:27.975 --> 00:17:32.040
Yoon Tae-Min. he started
spending lots of money
buying gifts.

275
00:17:32.175 --> 00:17:36.714
For me too because he get
better job. better pay.

276
00:17:37.847 --> 00:17:39.315
This job.
What was it?

277
00:17:39.451 --> 00:17:41.655
He work for new company.

278
00:17:41.791 --> 00:17:42.788
Kuragin.

279
00:17:44.292 --> 00:17:48.391
Are you sure?
'Cause Kuragin. Helios.
they can only use union labor.

280
00:17:48.527 --> 00:17:50.898
They can't hire craters.

281
00:17:51.033 --> 00:17:52.369
Yes. I am sure.

282
00:17:53.072 --> 00:17:55.733
He work at night.
out on surface.

283
00:17:56.970 --> 00:17:59.605
Kuragin's not authorized
to do night surface work.

284
00:18:00.738 --> 00:18:03.840
Well. that's what he tell me.

285
00:18:03.975 --> 00:18:07.217
I ask what work with
but he wouldn't say.

286
00:18:09.545 --> 00:18:11.353
He seem afraid.

287
00:18:18.423 --> 00:18:20.428
[objects clinking]

288
00:18:23.159 --> 00:18:25.399
Ah. you were one hell
of a Cosmonaut.

289
00:18:25.534 --> 00:18:27.902
[exhales sharply]
I remember Mir-7.

290
00:18:28.038 --> 00:18:31.603
Damn near turned into a batch
of crispy marshmallows
on that one.

291
00:18:31.738 --> 00:18:34.374
Media blew a big melodrama
out of it.

292
00:18:34.509 --> 00:18:36.180
[sighs]
It was nothing really.

293
00:18:36.315 --> 00:18:38.608
You call it a solid
fuel oxygen generator

294
00:18:38.743 --> 00:18:40.644
spewing out
a three-foot column

295
00:18:40.780 --> 00:18:42.848
of molten bits
of metal and flames.

296
00:18:42.983 --> 00:18:45.590
- You call that nothing?
- [chuckles]
I was never worried.

297
00:18:45.725 --> 00:18:47.318
Please. join me.

298
00:18:47.921 --> 00:18:50.655
This is the most expensive
vodka on the market.

299
00:18:50.791 --> 00:18:53.329
It has little bits
of gold leaf in it.

300
00:18:53.464 --> 00:18:56.566
Well. what do you know?
Look at that.
Hmm.

301
00:18:57.569 --> 00:18:59.966
- Wait. Do we do
the whole thing?
- The whole thing.

302
00:19:00.101 --> 00:19:01.139
Oh. shit.

303
00:19:01.874 --> 00:19:03.101
[both speak Russian]

304
00:19:03.236 --> 00:19:04.241
[chuckles]

305
00:19:06.579 --> 00:19:07.610
[sniffs]

306
00:19:08.213 --> 00:19:09.470
- [clicks tongue]
- [coughs]

307
00:19:09.605 --> 00:19:10.612
[chuckles]

308
00:19:11.715 --> 00:19:14.112
- Well. Admiral. I would--
- [clears throat. coughs]

309
00:19:14.714 --> 00:19:15.943
I would love
to reminisce more

310
00:19:16.078 --> 00:19:17.582
but the tyranny
of my schedule

311
00:19:17.718 --> 00:19:18.918
demands we get down
to business.

312
00:19:19.054 --> 00:19:20.048
Absolutely.

313
00:19:21.260 --> 00:19:23.818
I wanted to talk to you
about Lee Jung-Gil.

314
00:19:23.953 --> 00:19:25.953
Ah.
[inhales sharply] Yes.

315
00:19:26.088 --> 00:19:28.966
I've know the man
for almost 20 years

316
00:19:29.101 --> 00:19:32.898
and I can tell you
without a shadow of a doubt.
he did not commit this murder.

317
00:19:33.033 --> 00:19:35.637
Well. that's something
for the courts to decide. no?

318
00:19:35.773 --> 00:19:38.273
The Mars Charter states that
any resident has the right

319
00:19:38.408 --> 00:19:39.837
to a hearing
on Happy Valley...

320
00:19:39.972 --> 00:19:41.376
[stammers] ...before
they get sent back.

321
00:19:41.512 --> 00:19:44.039
- Every legal resident. yes.
- [scoffs]

322
00:19:44.175 --> 00:19:47.383
But Lee is not a legal resident
and nor is his wife.

323
00:19:47.985 --> 00:19:50.985
And their status
is at the discretion
of the base leadership.

324
00:19:51.121 --> 00:19:52.520
In other words. you.

325
00:19:53.587 --> 00:19:55.793
Huh?
It was my decision.

326
00:19:56.529 --> 00:19:59.293
So change your decision.
Governor.
[chuckles]

327
00:19:59.429 --> 00:20:04.433
Because I can tell you
there is no chance that Lee
had anything to do with this.

328
00:20:06.099 --> 00:20:09.800
[stutters] You remember our...
our first Mars crew

329
00:20:09.935 --> 00:20:12.371
that got stranded here
for 18 months?

330
00:20:12.506 --> 00:20:14.145
Yes. Yes. we all followed that.

331
00:20:14.280 --> 00:20:16.647
It was a miracle
any of you survived.

332
00:20:16.782 --> 00:20:21.308
Well. miracle...
Lee was one of the
main reasons we did.

333
00:20:21.878 --> 00:20:24.188
You know. towards
the end of the mission.
most of the crew got sick.

334
00:20:24.323 --> 00:20:26.854
And when our life support
went down.

335
00:20:27.524 --> 00:20:31.662
Lee was the one
who got it back online.

336
00:20:31.798 --> 00:20:35.099
Even though he'd
never seen anything
but the Soviet systems

337
00:20:35.235 --> 00:20:36.729
that y'all sold
to his country.

338
00:20:36.864 --> 00:20:39.237
So. without Lee
we would've all been dead

339
00:20:39.372 --> 00:20:42.067
and there would be
no colony here today.

340
00:20:42.203 --> 00:20:43.536
[sighs]

341
00:20:43.671 --> 00:20:46.201
Well. I'm glad you...
[sighs]

342
00:20:46.336 --> 00:20:51.543
...brought up his past
as an important context...

343
00:20:51.678 --> 00:20:52.914
Thank you.
...to his case.

344
00:20:53.049 --> 00:20:54.549
Yes. Yes.

345
00:20:55.712 --> 00:20:56.716
[inhales sharply]

346
00:20:58.787 --> 00:21:03.024
Isn't it true that
Lee Jung-Gil threatened

347
00:21:03.159 --> 00:21:06.990
Commander Poole and your
friend Gregory Kuznetsov
with a pistol?

348
00:21:07.858 --> 00:21:09.763
Uh... Well. yeah. well...

349
00:21:09.898 --> 00:21:12.460
he-he was on a military mission
and he didn't know. uh--

350
00:21:12.595 --> 00:21:16.732
And didn't Poole and Kuznetsov
have to forcibly disarm him?

351
00:21:16.868 --> 00:21:20.537
Force... well... [stammers]
Technically they had to...
But-But he didn't--

352
00:21:20.672 --> 00:21:24.074
And wasn't that gun
later used to shoot
Commander Danielle Poole?

353
00:21:24.210 --> 00:21:25.873
Now listen. Molly had nothing
to do with it. It--

354
00:21:26.008 --> 00:21:28.483
Who?
No...
Lee. Lee.

355
00:21:28.619 --> 00:21:30.377
Was he not one
of the main instigators

356
00:21:30.513 --> 00:21:32.214
of the riot that resulted
in that gun being fired?

357
00:21:32.349 --> 00:21:34.217
L-Listen. you're getting it
all twisted. Just...

358
00:21:34.352 --> 00:21:36.120
Wait. wait a sec.
That monitor
on your ankle.

359
00:21:36.256 --> 00:21:38.925
You are sentenced to wearing
it as the result of your own

360
00:21:39.060 --> 00:21:41.623
criminal actions during
that insurrection. correct?

361
00:21:41.758 --> 00:21:44.192
Listen to me.
you son of a bitch.
I'm not a goddamn criminal!

362
00:21:50.842 --> 00:21:51.969
[sighs]

363
00:21:55.177 --> 00:21:56.204
Admiral...

364
00:21:59.076 --> 00:22:01.275
I'm afraid we are
out of time.

365
00:22:03.614 --> 00:22:05.081
[Ed sighs]

366
00:22:11.859 --> 00:22:14.662
- [door opens. shuts]
- [sighs]

367
00:22:21.467 --> 00:22:23.968
[radio chatter]

368
00:22:32.678 --> 00:22:34.077
Congratulations. Walt.

369
00:22:34.811 --> 00:22:38.015
Oh. Thanks. Kelly.

370
00:22:38.151 --> 00:22:41.755
It's a... a start
but it's promising.
For sure.

371
00:22:43.123 --> 00:22:45.555
I heard you were having trouble
with your S.E.E.K.E.R.s.

372
00:22:45.691 --> 00:22:48.559
I spent a lot of time
with those bots and I'd
be happy to help.

373
00:22:48.695 --> 00:22:51.696
They're stone dead.
They went dark before
the sequencer could transmit

374
00:22:51.832 --> 00:22:53.493
a complete backbone
chain analysis.

375
00:22:53.629 --> 00:22:56.033
So. if this means what
we hope it means... [sighs]

376
00:22:56.168 --> 00:22:58.032
...have to confirm it
on the next mission.

377
00:22:58.601 --> 00:23:00.336
Have you thought about
who's gonna be on your crew?

378
00:23:01.506 --> 00:23:04.580
Uh. crew? We're sending
another set of robotic probes.

379
00:23:06.312 --> 00:23:09.382
S-Seriously? [scoffs]
We don't have time for that.

380
00:23:09.518 --> 00:23:12.880
Some of us actually
pay attention to the company
exploration protocols.

381
00:23:13.016 --> 00:23:15.983
Probes first. people second.
And only if warranted
by probe results.

382
00:23:16.485 --> 00:23:18.589
But you're about
to give up our advantage.

383
00:23:19.325 --> 00:23:22.199
You know there are other
companies looking at Titan.

384
00:23:22.334 --> 00:23:26.465
If you really did find life.
it's only a matter of time
before they will too.

385
00:23:27.134 --> 00:23:29.132
I don't need you to tell me
how to do my job.

386
00:23:30.401 --> 00:23:32.872
Why don't you focus
on your precious little crater?

387
00:23:35.673 --> 00:23:36.942
[sighs]

388
00:23:40.882 --> 00:23:43.187
Walt. this isn't
about me or you.

389
00:23:43.322 --> 00:23:45.219
It's about Helios.
[sighs]

390
00:23:45.355 --> 00:23:47.019
We can't blow this.

391
00:23:47.154 --> 00:23:48.921
If another company gets
their hands on it first.

392
00:23:49.056 --> 00:23:50.825
they'll be the ones
to reap the rewards.

393
00:23:50.960 --> 00:23:53.220
We'll lose valuable time
if we send another set

394
00:23:53.355 --> 00:23:54.861
of glitchy
S.E.E.K.E.R. robots.

395
00:23:58.171 --> 00:23:59.734
Humans need to do this.

396
00:24:01.337 --> 00:24:02.998
Oh. I get it.

397
00:24:03.567 --> 00:24:06.174
You're pushing a manned mission
because you wanna be on it.

398
00:24:07.110 --> 00:24:09.040
That's not what I--
I won't go
with a crewed mission

399
00:24:09.175 --> 00:24:11.311
until I have verification
of my results.

400
00:24:11.447 --> 00:24:12.880
That's how it works.

401
00:24:13.983 --> 00:24:16.751
Now. if you'll excuse me.
We have work to do.

402
00:24:17.781 --> 00:24:19.314
[sighs]

403
00:24:29.000 --> 00:24:29.956
[blows]

404
00:24:30.092 --> 00:24:31.067
What is he thinking?

405
00:24:31.202 --> 00:24:32.267
A robotic mission?

406
00:24:32.403 --> 00:24:34.000
[scoffs] I mean. hello.

407
00:24:34.135 --> 00:24:37.239
you think Kuragin is just
gonna bide its time?

408
00:24:38.242 --> 00:24:40.234
[scoffs] They're gonna
snatch life right out
from under us.

409
00:24:40.370 --> 00:24:42.008
Wait. what are you
talking about?

410
00:24:42.143 --> 00:24:44.211
I told Walt the next mission
should be manned.

411
00:24:44.346 --> 00:24:46.212
- And do you know what
he actually said? [scoffs]
- No.

412
00:24:46.348 --> 00:24:48.581
That what I really wanted was
to go on the mission to Titan.

413
00:24:48.717 --> 00:24:50.083
Yeah.
Well. don't you?

414
00:24:50.819 --> 00:24:53.247
No. No. I am
strictly concerned

415
00:24:53.383 --> 00:24:55.092
with the best
scientific approach.

416
00:24:55.228 --> 00:24:57.459
[chuckles]
What?

417
00:24:58.428 --> 00:25:00.759
- Mom. you totally wanna go.
- Yeah. I don't buy
that shit at all.

418
00:25:00.894 --> 00:25:02.695
[chuckles]
No. I don't. Okay?

419
00:25:02.831 --> 00:25:04.133
And that's
beside the point.

420
00:25:04.769 --> 00:25:06.968
All right. he doesn't want
a manned mission

421
00:25:07.104 --> 00:25:11.301
and even if he did. he doesn't
need another exobiologist.

422
00:25:11.803 --> 00:25:15.374
[stammers] Well.
you're still an aviator.
right? Be their pilot.

423
00:25:15.509 --> 00:25:18.374
Dad. I haven't flown
in years.
It's like riding a bike.

424
00:25:18.510 --> 00:25:21.250
If you want something.
don't take no for an answer.

425
00:25:21.385 --> 00:25:23.248
Also you're a Baldwin.

426
00:25:23.383 --> 00:25:26.048
If things get a little tough.
you roll the hard six.

427
00:25:26.183 --> 00:25:27.921
Come on. Alex.
Back me up here.

428
00:25:29.154 --> 00:25:30.727
- Roll the... the what?
- Hard six.

429
00:25:30.862 --> 00:25:33.588
I hear you. Dad.
but technically
Walt is right.

430
00:25:34.425 --> 00:25:36.029
You know. it is safer
if we just send

431
00:25:36.164 --> 00:25:38.331
another round
of robotic probes.
Safer?

432
00:25:38.467 --> 00:25:42.305
Now that's exactly the attitude
that fucked us on<i> Apollo 10</i> .

433
00:25:42.440 --> 00:25:44.839
When NASA stopped taking risks.

434
00:25:45.707 --> 00:25:47.171
That's why we lost the moon.

435
00:25:49.775 --> 00:25:51.109
[Ed grumbles]

436
00:25:57.355 --> 00:26:00.789
I mean. why am I even
giving this guy the power
to say no to me?

437
00:26:01.992 --> 00:26:04.424
- Exactly. No.
- He doesn't get the last say.

438
00:26:04.560 --> 00:26:06.993
That patronizing prick.

439
00:26:08.793 --> 00:26:09.765
Yeah. Mom.

440
00:26:10.434 --> 00:26:11.529
I'll see you guys later.

441
00:26:11.664 --> 00:26:13.399
Attagirl.

442
00:26:13.535 --> 00:26:14.803
[door closes]

443
00:26:18.204 --> 00:26:19.643
So. what are you
gonna do about Lee?

444
00:26:21.207 --> 00:26:23.572
[groans] I'll figure
something out.

445
00:26:23.708 --> 00:26:26.713
- I wanna help.
- [chuckles] Yeah.
sure you do.

446
00:26:26.848 --> 00:26:28.984
- I really do. No?
- No.

447
00:26:29.120 --> 00:26:31.512
I've been trying to get you
to give a shit for years...

448
00:26:32.790 --> 00:26:34.583
Suddenly now
you wanna help out?

449
00:26:34.718 --> 00:26:37.358
Can't even be bothered
to go to a single SDM meeting.

450
00:26:37.493 --> 00:26:40.393
That was before everything
happened with Lee.
I really want to.

451
00:26:40.528 --> 00:26:45.066
What you want is to do
whatever it is you feel
like in the moment.

452
00:26:45.201 --> 00:26:47.196
See. that's the problem
with your whole generation.

453
00:26:47.332 --> 00:26:50.473
You're so self-centered.
It's me. me. me.

454
00:26:51.410 --> 00:26:55.237
Why don't you just
run around on your beach
in your little video games

455
00:26:55.373 --> 00:26:57.340
and let the adults
handle this. all right?

456
00:27:02.414 --> 00:27:04.549
Yeah. You can be a real
asshole sometimes.

457
00:27:04.685 --> 00:27:05.815
You know that?

458
00:27:05.950 --> 00:27:07.757
[stammers] Alex.

459
00:27:09.954 --> 00:27:11.761
[door closes]

460
00:27:21.503 --> 00:27:23.698
- [Fred]<i> You still</i>
<i> out chasing ducks?</i>
- [Celia] Nah.

461
00:27:23.833 --> 00:27:25.908
-<i> Liar.</i>
- What do you want.
Stanislaus?

462
00:27:26.043 --> 00:27:28.241
<i> Uh. a supermodel wife</i>
<i> and three kids?</i>

463
00:27:28.377 --> 00:27:31.638
- You're not my type.
-<i> Oh. I know. but you asked.</i>

464
00:27:31.774 --> 00:27:33.477
<i> Hey. I caught prisoner</i>
<i> escort duty tomorrow.</i>

465
00:27:33.612 --> 00:27:35.379
<i> You want anything</i>
<i> from the Phoenix Exchange?</i>

466
00:27:35.515 --> 00:27:37.918
Yeah. dental floss.
Get me two. I'll pay you back.

467
00:27:38.054 --> 00:27:39.986
<i> Yeah. not necessary.</i>
<i> I gotcha.</i>

468
00:27:40.121 --> 00:27:41.923
-<i> Night. partner.</i>
- Good night.

469
00:27:46.532 --> 00:27:48.424
[boosters firing in distance]

470
00:28:36.814 --> 00:28:38.241
I know you two have
your differences.

471
00:28:38.377 --> 00:28:39.917
but you are the best
that we have.

472
00:28:40.052 --> 00:28:42.347
And sometimes differences
lead to the best results.

473
00:28:42.482 --> 00:28:45.449
So you guys need to figure
this out. Kelly's right.

474
00:28:45.584 --> 00:28:47.725
A crewed mission to Titan
makes the most sense.

475
00:28:52.054 --> 00:28:54.924
Walt. you'll command.
Your expertise on Titan
is essential.

476
00:28:55.827 --> 00:28:58.367
- Kelly will be your pilot.
- What? She doesn't have--

477
00:28:58.502 --> 00:29:01.265
Dr. Baldwin happens to be
a crack naval aviator
from way back.

478
00:29:01.400 --> 00:29:03.741
As her father
constantly reminds me.

479
00:29:05.069 --> 00:29:06.172
Now get to it.

480
00:29:07.344 --> 00:29:08.636
[sighs]

481
00:29:09.809 --> 00:29:11.012
Yes. sir.

482
00:29:13.078 --> 00:29:14.312
You won't regret this.

483
00:29:17.420 --> 00:29:18.613
Walt.

484
00:29:20.416 --> 00:29:23.718
I wouldn't have forced
the issue unless I truly
believed in this mission.

485
00:29:23.854 --> 00:29:25.821
- Look. I'm sure we'll--
- You're so full of shit.

486
00:29:26.757 --> 00:29:29.524
Excuse me?
The only reason
you're part of this

487
00:29:29.660 --> 00:29:31.263
is 'cause you're
part owner of Helios.

488
00:29:32.332 --> 00:29:35.366
But you know what?
I'll make it work

489
00:29:35.502 --> 00:29:37.907
because I believe in this
even more than you do.

490
00:29:41.540 --> 00:29:43.277
[Ed]<i> The plain</i>
<i> and simple fact is that</i>

491
00:29:43.413 --> 00:29:45.873
tomorrow morning Lee Jung-Gil
gets sent back to Earth

492
00:29:46.008 --> 00:29:48.844
unless the people in this room
do something about it.

493
00:29:48.979 --> 00:29:51.080
What can we do? I mean.
you've already spoken
to the governor.

494
00:29:51.849 --> 00:29:56.090
No. no. We need to take
matters into our own hands.

495
00:29:57.860 --> 00:29:58.862
We need to break him out.

496
00:30:00.064 --> 00:30:01.755
- Now we're talking.
- [Malka] Mm-hmm.

497
00:30:01.891 --> 00:30:04.560
- That's right.
- Guys. come on.
That's too far.

498
00:30:04.695 --> 00:30:09.264
Look. I'm on Lee's side
as much as anybody here.

499
00:30:09.400 --> 00:30:12.976
but what you're talking about
is exactly how things spiral
out of control.

500
00:30:13.111 --> 00:30:16.237
If we do nothing.
Lee could get hurt or killed.

501
00:30:16.373 --> 00:30:19.244
Even if you do come up
with a way to get him
out of custody. what then?

502
00:30:19.379 --> 00:30:21.346
You gonna hide him
somewhere forever?

503
00:30:21.481 --> 00:30:23.745
- [Miles] Right.
- Yeah. Palmer. the governor...

504
00:30:23.880 --> 00:30:25.979
Look. they wouldn't let up
until they find him.

505
00:30:26.115 --> 00:30:29.455
and then they'll
just arrest everyone
who ever talked to Lee.

506
00:30:29.591 --> 00:30:31.552
And then send us all back
down to Earth. including Lee.

507
00:30:31.687 --> 00:30:33.263
We gotta be smart
about this.

508
00:30:34.232 --> 00:30:36.493
- You gone soft. Miles?
- [Ed] Oh. leave him alone.

509
00:30:36.628 --> 00:30:38.761
Look. I understand
their concerns. I do.

510
00:30:38.896 --> 00:30:41.434
I mean. what we're talking
about here is a big risk.

511
00:30:42.571 --> 00:30:46.437
so whoever doesn't wanna be
a part should walk away now.

512
00:30:58.918 --> 00:31:00.187
I'm sorry.

513
00:31:01.627 --> 00:31:03.091
It's okay.
[scoffs]

514
00:31:05.188 --> 00:31:06.391
[Ed] It's okay.

515
00:31:13.496 --> 00:31:14.866
- [sighs]
- [door closes]

516
00:31:15.002 --> 00:31:16.730
[sighs] Fucking cowards.

517
00:31:16.865 --> 00:31:18.833
[Ed] Trust me.
It's better this way.

518
00:31:18.968 --> 00:31:21.142
Listen. the word is.
Lee gets shipped off-planet

519
00:31:21.277 --> 00:31:23.639
in less than 20 hours.
so whatever we do.

520
00:31:23.774 --> 00:31:26.314
it's gotta come together
right fucking now.

521
00:31:27.150 --> 00:31:29.277
Well. we can't break
into the holding cells.

522
00:31:29.413 --> 00:31:30.985
We've all been in there.

523
00:31:31.121 --> 00:31:33.153
Hmm. Too many MPKs.
Too many guns.

524
00:31:33.288 --> 00:31:35.284
Yeah. well. w-we gotta
engineer this in a way

525
00:31:35.419 --> 00:31:36.983
without making
anyone famous.

526
00:31:38.086 --> 00:31:42.125
We gotta find the weakness
in their chains somehow.

527
00:31:42.861 --> 00:31:46.093
You know. when I was locked up.
the guards got most worried

528
00:31:46.229 --> 00:31:49.766
when they had to
take us to court.
That makes sense.

529
00:31:49.901 --> 00:31:52.033
You're more vulnerable
when you're out in the world.

530
00:31:52.169 --> 00:31:54.638
Yeah. like when they take Lee
out to move him up to Phoenix.

531
00:31:54.773 --> 00:31:57.879
- That's right.
- So what? We hijack a hopper?

532
00:31:58.014 --> 00:32:00.445
- That's crazy.
- Maybe not.

533
00:32:00.581 --> 00:32:03.248
I'm not on rota
to fly to Phoenix tomorrow.

534
00:32:03.384 --> 00:32:04.720
but I think I can swap
with Hansen.

535
00:32:04.855 --> 00:32:06.984
Well. then we got a hopper.

536
00:32:07.119 --> 00:32:10.684
- Ronnie. you still have
access to the motor pool?
- Sure do.

537
00:32:10.819 --> 00:32:12.887
Well. now we're
cooking with gas.

538
00:32:13.022 --> 00:32:15.792
But how do we even
get him away from the MPKs?

539
00:32:15.928 --> 00:32:17.132
[groans]

540
00:32:18.934 --> 00:32:20.465
I think I got something.

541
00:32:33.341 --> 00:32:36.949
[Celia] Excuse me.
What can I do
for you. Officer?

542
00:32:37.085 --> 00:32:39.913
Uh. I need to speak
to whoever's in charge
of your employee records.

543
00:32:41.218 --> 00:32:42.751
Concerning?

544
00:32:43.719 --> 00:32:45.892
Concerning. uh. Yoon Tae-Min.

545
00:32:46.028 --> 00:32:50.691
Uh. Mr. Yoon is reported
to have done some night
surface work for Kuragin.

546
00:32:50.827 --> 00:32:53.368
and. uh. I need to know
what he was doing.

547
00:32:53.504 --> 00:32:57.733
Isn't that sort
of inquiry usually done
by an investigator?

548
00:32:58.967 --> 00:33:01.308
Well. today
it's being done by me.

549
00:33:04.907 --> 00:33:06.479
I'm sorry.
but you wasted your time.

550
00:33:06.614 --> 00:33:10.218
There is no night surface work
done by Kuragin.

551
00:33:14.084 --> 00:33:17.058
A hopper landed last night
near the space elevator.

552
00:33:17.194 --> 00:33:18.959
and cargo was seen
being unloaded.

553
00:33:19.662 --> 00:33:23.462
Cargo that doesn't appear
on any official base manifest.

554
00:33:28.866 --> 00:33:31.768
We have no such shipments
as you describe.

555
00:33:31.903 --> 00:33:34.534
So. I need to know
what you're bringing down here

556
00:33:34.670 --> 00:33:36.209
and what that cargo was.

557
00:33:36.345 --> 00:33:38.444
Tomas. our guest
was just leaving.

558
00:33:44.285 --> 00:33:45.946
Have a nice sol.
Officer.

559
00:33:50.286 --> 00:33:53.090
[voice on PA system]
<i> The entry port is off limits.</i>

560
00:33:53.226 --> 00:33:57.367
[MPK officer] Can't do anything
if any of you do not leave
right fucking now.

561
00:33:58.037 --> 00:34:00.698
Okay. All clear
for prisoner transport.

562
00:34:00.833 --> 00:34:02.699
[Palmer. on radio]
<i> Copy that. Almost there.</i>

563
00:34:09.577 --> 00:34:11.345
- Whoa. whoa. whoa. whoa.
- Whoa. Hold on.

564
00:34:12.247 --> 00:34:13.710
It's okay.
Give them a minute.

565
00:34:16.147 --> 00:34:17.516
[sobs]

566
00:34:18.854 --> 00:34:20.288
[in Korean]

567
00:34:51.216 --> 00:34:53.486
[sobbing]

568
00:34:57.222 --> 00:34:58.624
[sobbing]

569
00:34:59.694 --> 00:35:02.159
[in English] All right. Lee.
It's time to go.

570
00:35:02.295 --> 00:35:04.992
[sobbing. sniffling]

571
00:35:19.211 --> 00:35:20.678
[radio chatter]

572
00:35:22.687 --> 00:35:24.053
Boss around?

573
00:35:24.189 --> 00:35:26.248
Entry port.
They're moving Lee.

574
00:35:26.383 --> 00:35:29.253
Uh. prisoner transport
wasn't scheduled
for another hour.

575
00:35:29.756 --> 00:35:32.228
Moved it up.
Oh. shit.
All right.

576
00:35:38.033 --> 00:35:39.367
Here. Sit down.

577
00:35:40.903 --> 00:35:42.062
[clears throat]

578
00:35:44.142 --> 00:35:47.137
Hey. Spano.
You think they got floss

579
00:35:47.272 --> 00:35:50.409
- up at their PX up
on Phoenix?
- I don't floss. man.

580
00:35:50.545 --> 00:35:53.313
- You don't what?
- Floss. I don't floss.

581
00:35:53.449 --> 00:35:55.647
[Fred] You don't floss?
Out of principle?

582
00:35:55.783 --> 00:35:58.647
Brother. gum disease is real.
It'll get ya.

583
00:35:58.782 --> 00:36:01.481
Hey.
Pressure is dropping.

584
00:36:01.617 --> 00:36:03.120
[sighs] What?

585
00:36:03.255 --> 00:36:04.920
[beeping]

586
00:36:06.061 --> 00:36:07.395
What the hell?

587
00:36:11.600 --> 00:36:13.036
Hey. What are you guys
doing up there?

588
00:36:13.172 --> 00:36:14.495
We're losing pressure
back here.

589
00:36:15.031 --> 00:36:17.033
Hey! We're losing pressure
back here.

590
00:36:18.136 --> 00:36:22.243
[shouting. muffled]
Transport One? Transport One!

591
00:36:22.379 --> 00:36:23.906
Have 'em contact
the protester's family.

592
00:36:24.042 --> 00:36:25.910
Sir. can I talk to you
before they take off?

593
00:36:26.045 --> 00:36:27.813
They're already on board.
Rover's about to separate.

594
00:36:27.948 --> 00:36:29.814
Yes. sir. Uh. there's
something going on at Kuragin.

595
00:36:29.949 --> 00:36:31.683
I think it might be connected
to Yoon's death.

596
00:36:31.819 --> 00:36:34.120
- What is it?
- Well. I don't know exactly.

597
00:36:34.255 --> 00:36:36.987
But they're covering
something up. Lee might not
be the right guy.

598
00:36:37.123 --> 00:36:38.794
[Fred. on radio]<i> 10-99.</i>
<i> 10-99. Officers need help.</i>

599
00:36:39.530 --> 00:36:41.598
- I need a sitrep.
- [Fred]<i> We need help!</i>

600
00:36:41.733 --> 00:36:43.298
[panting] Shit.

601
00:36:43.434 --> 00:36:46.135
Equalization valve
is broken. [panting]

602
00:36:46.270 --> 00:36:48.997
- [alarm blaring]
- [groaning]

603
00:36:52.210 --> 00:36:53.336
- Oxygen.
- Check the tanks.

604
00:36:53.472 --> 00:36:55.173
[muffled] Get the tanks.

605
00:36:55.309 --> 00:36:56.477
[Spano] It's empty.

606
00:36:59.179 --> 00:37:00.745
[groaning]

607
00:37:03.447 --> 00:37:05.684
[panting]

608
00:37:07.617 --> 00:37:09.457
[PA system chimes]

609
00:37:11.690 --> 00:37:14.060
<i> - Warning.</i>
- Jesus.

610
00:37:14.195 --> 00:37:17.394
PK Transport One. we have
officers trapped in there.
Respond.

611
00:37:17.530 --> 00:37:18.833
[strains] I can't get in.

612
00:37:18.968 --> 00:37:20.028
[Celia] Respond!

613
00:37:21.530 --> 00:37:22.503
What?

614
00:37:23.038 --> 00:37:24.373
Ed Baldwin?

615
00:37:26.543 --> 00:37:28.707
[Ed] We're good to disconnect.
Here we go.

616
00:37:30.705 --> 00:37:31.776
Let's go.

617
00:37:37.579 --> 00:37:41.422
Dispatch. I need
every patrol rover
after PK Transport One.

618
00:37:41.558 --> 00:37:44.350
Stop them and execute
emergency entry.

619
00:37:44.486 --> 00:37:47.122
- [dispatcher]<i> Copy that.</i>
- ATC. Sheriff James.

620
00:37:47.257 --> 00:37:49.057
Do you have eyes on the rover
leaving gate six?

621
00:37:49.193 --> 00:37:50.662
[ATC specialist 1]
<i> Affirmative. Sheriff.</i>

622
00:37:50.797 --> 00:37:52.700
<i> It's headed</i>
<i> toward the hopper pads.</i>

623
00:37:52.836 --> 00:37:55.031
Suit up. I need all my pilots
out there in hoppers now.

624
00:37:55.166 --> 00:37:56.706
I'm not letting these fuckers
get out of here.

625
00:37:56.841 --> 00:37:57.835
Yes. sir.

626
00:38:07.249 --> 00:38:08.483
[Ed] How's he doing?

627
00:38:12.351 --> 00:38:14.389
- Pulse is fine.
but he's still out.
- [Ed] All right.

628
00:38:14.525 --> 00:38:15.952
Pressure's coming back up.
Uncuff Lee.

629
00:38:24.059 --> 00:38:25.929
- [rumbling]
- [grunts]

630
00:38:33.301 --> 00:38:35.070
- [groaning]
- [Ed] What was that?

631
00:38:35.714 --> 00:38:37.446
[groans]

632
00:38:40.542 --> 00:38:43.318
Hold all air traffic.
Nothing flies unless I say so.

633
00:38:43.454 --> 00:38:45.414
- Yes. Governor.
- Where are they?

634
00:38:45.549 --> 00:38:48.855
Heading to pad five.
cargo hopper.
Hold all air traffic.

635
00:38:48.991 --> 00:38:50.519
- Understood?
- [ATC specialist 2]
Yes. ma'am.

636
00:38:50.655 --> 00:38:52.289
All flights stand down.

637
00:38:52.424 --> 00:38:53.429
Goddamn it.

638
00:39:04.304 --> 00:39:05.336
[in Portuguese]

639
00:39:05.472 --> 00:39:06.935
[breathing heavily]

640
00:39:07.071 --> 00:39:08.411
[in English]
I'll never make it.

641
00:39:09.480 --> 00:39:11.480
I don't think I can
fly the hopper.

642
00:39:16.284 --> 00:39:17.684
Then I'll fly.

643
00:39:20.258 --> 00:39:25.026
- Are you sure? I thought you
weren't supposed to fly.
- Of course I'm sure.

644
00:39:25.161 --> 00:39:27.287
[in Scottish accent]
I didn't get all dressed up
for nothing.

645
00:39:30.131 --> 00:39:33.370
[sighs] You think you can drive
the rover clear of the plume?

646
00:39:34.437 --> 00:39:37.169
- Yeah.
- Good. All right.

647
00:39:37.304 --> 00:39:39.701
Lee. Hey.

648
00:39:39.837 --> 00:39:41.304
Wake up.
[grunts]

649
00:39:42.040 --> 00:39:44.136
Okay.
Yeah.
Well. wake up.

650
00:39:44.272 --> 00:39:45.645
[chuckles]
Come on.
I'm okay.

651
00:39:45.780 --> 00:39:47.778
- [Ed] Yeah. yeah.
- Dispatch. James.

652
00:39:47.914 --> 00:39:49.509
Where the hell
are my air assets?

653
00:39:49.644 --> 00:39:51.112
[dispatcher]<i> Heading</i>
<i> to our hoppers now. sir.</i>

654
00:39:51.247 --> 00:39:53.082
Tell 'em to get
their asses in gear.

655
00:39:53.785 --> 00:39:54.919
[Ed] Full internal power.

656
00:39:55.453 --> 00:39:56.591
Okay.

657
00:39:57.060 --> 00:39:59.055
[engine starts]

658
00:39:59.623 --> 00:40:00.826
Here we go.

659
00:40:21.284 --> 00:40:23.580
[Ed coughs. mutters]

660
00:40:23.716 --> 00:40:27.688
Those son of a bitches...
[coughs] ...are right
behind us. [coughs]

661
00:40:32.560 --> 00:40:35.196
[Palmer. on radio]
<i> PK Air Four. Command.</i>
<i> Give me your status.</i>

662
00:40:35.331 --> 00:40:38.633
Command. Air Four.
We got eyes on 'em.
but we're pushing red line.

663
00:40:38.768 --> 00:40:41.537
Do not lose them.
Exceed red line if you have to.

664
00:40:41.673 --> 00:40:45.101
You've got MPK Air Two inbound
at your 4:00.

665
00:40:46.436 --> 00:40:48.234
[Lenya] Are they trying for
Korolev Crater?

666
00:40:48.370 --> 00:40:50.313
Korolev is north.
Only thing that way is--

667
00:40:50.448 --> 00:40:53.839
ISN Compound.
Son of a bitch.

668
00:40:54.342 --> 00:40:57.418
<i> Boyd. he can't reach</i>
<i> that base. They don't have</i>
<i> an extradition treaty</i>

669
00:40:57.553 --> 00:40:59.181
<i> - with the M-6.</i>
- Wilco.

670
00:41:00.519 --> 00:41:01.887
[Ed coughs]

671
00:41:03.588 --> 00:41:05.924
[coughing]

672
00:41:16.875 --> 00:41:17.940
[coughs]

673
00:41:18.075 --> 00:41:19.575
[wheezes]

674
00:41:32.689 --> 00:41:34.784
[Celia] Sir.
we're gaining on them.

675
00:41:34.920 --> 00:41:36.757
[Palmer]<i> Good. Stay on it.</i>

676
00:41:38.019 --> 00:41:40.222
[coughs. wheezes]

677
00:41:46.227 --> 00:41:49.235
[Palmer. on radio]<i> Ed.</i>
<i> surrender now and you</i>
<i> won't be harmed.</i>

678
00:41:49.370 --> 00:41:51.739
Son of a bitch.

679
00:41:53.376 --> 00:41:55.239
[groans. pants] Lee.

680
00:41:56.075 --> 00:41:59.144
It's time for you
to head below. Suit up.

681
00:41:59.279 --> 00:42:01.142
As soon as we touch down.
I'm gonna kill the engine.

682
00:42:01.278 --> 00:42:02.579
give you enough time
to drop down.

683
00:42:02.715 --> 00:42:04.818
[wheezing. coughing]

684
00:42:06.757 --> 00:42:08.822
What about you?
Don't worry about me.

685
00:42:10.193 --> 00:42:11.286
[in Korean]

686
00:42:17.761 --> 00:42:20.328
[automated voice]<i> Warning.</i>
<i> Landing beacon not acquired.</i>

687
00:42:25.336 --> 00:42:27.676
<i> Warning. Landing beacon</i>
<i> not acquired.</i>

688
00:42:34.817 --> 00:42:36.485
[in English] Command.
MPK Air Four.

689
00:42:36.621 --> 00:42:38.181
Their hopper's landing
near ISN.

690
00:42:38.317 --> 00:42:41.514
Stay on 'em. We cannot
let them reach that base.

691
00:42:50.168 --> 00:42:52.162
[Lee panting]

692
00:43:05.007 --> 00:43:06.908
[MPK officer]
<i> He's making a break</i>
<i> for the ISN base air lock.</i>

693
00:43:07.044 --> 00:43:08.508
<i> We're pursuing on foot.</i>

694
00:43:32.409 --> 00:43:33.905
All right. Admiral.

695
00:43:34.041 --> 00:43:36.943
Show's over.
Let me see your hands.

696
00:43:44.748 --> 00:43:46.018
Admiral.

697
00:43:48.885 --> 00:43:50.286
Come on now.

698
00:43:52.396 --> 00:43:53.762
Please don't make me...

699
00:44:02.933 --> 00:44:04.606
Air Four. PK Boyd.

